#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:4
msgid "cmake-diagnostics(7)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:7
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:13
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:17
msgid ""
"CMake Diagnostics are the mechanism by which CMake categorizes and presents "
"certain advisory information about a project's configuration and the "
"generation of its build system.  These diagnostics can be seen as the build "
"system equivalent of compiler warnings.  Diagnostics provide feedback on "
"potential issues in several categories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:23
msgid "Issues that may impact the success of the build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:25
msgid "Issues that may impact the correctness of the build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:27
msgid "Issues that may impact the correctness of the project packaging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:29
msgid ""
"Issues that may impact the ability of the project to be built with newer "
"versions of dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:32
msgid ""
"Issues that may impact the ability of the project to be built with newer "
"versions of CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:36
msgid "Diagnostic Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:38
msgid ""
"The action taken when a particular diagnostic is triggered depends on the "
"diagnostic category.  Most categories will warn by default.  The :command:"
"`cmake_diagnostic` command and :option:`-W <cmake -W>` options can be used "
"to control what action occurs when a diagnostic of a particular category is "
"triggered.  The possible actions are described in the documentation of the "
"same."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:46
msgid "Diagnostic Categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:48
msgid "The following categories are defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:51
msgid "``CMD_AUTHOR`` (``-Wauthor``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:0
msgid "Default"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:53
#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:69
#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:85
msgid "Warn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:55
msgid ""
"Warn about a build system's incorrect use of CMake, or of a CMake interface "
"provided by a dependency.  This is the category triggered by :command:"
"`message(AUTHOR_WARNING)`.  It is also the ancestor of many other diagnostic "
"categories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:60
msgid ""
"The most important aspect of this category is that it represents issues with "
"a project's build system which typically require alteration to the same.  "
"This is to say that users simply trying to build a project obtained "
"elsewhere will typically not be interested in these warnings, except to "
"perhaps report them to the project's developer(s)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:67
msgid "``CMD_DEPRECATED`` (``-Wdeprecated``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:0
msgid "Parent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:70
msgid "``CMD_AUTHOR``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:72
msgid ""
"Warn about use of a deprecated function or package.  This is the category "
"triggered by :command:`message(DEPRECATION)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:76
msgid "``CMD_UNINITIALIZED`` (``-Wuninitialized``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:78
msgid "Ignore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:80
msgid "Warn if an uninitialized variable is dereferenced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:83
msgid "``CMD_UNUSED_CLI`` (``-Wunused-cli``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:87
msgid ""
"Warn about variables that are declared on the command line, but not used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-diagnostics.7.rst:89
msgid ""
"Although the action of this warning category can be queried as usual, "
"changes made using the :command:`cmake_diagnostic` command have no effect."
msgstr ""
